# HTML
## form

The `FORM` is a normal, block element that is used to submit user input to a url.

||code html||
<body>
	<form action="/save" method="POST" >
		...
	</form>
</body>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## input

The `INPUT` tag is a void, inline element that can accept user input. The `type` attribute determines its behavior.

||code html||
<body>
	<input type="text" />
	<input type="checkbox" />
	<input type="submit" />
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<input type="text" />
<input type="checkbox" />
<input type="submit" />
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## button

The `BUTTON` tag is a normal, inline element that can also work with a `FORM`. The `type` attribute determines its behavior.

||code html||
<body>
	<button type="submit" >Save</button>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<button type="submit" >Save</button>
</div>


[slide]
